items.title: January jobs report will be released on Feb. 11 after shutdown delay
items.description: The January jobs report delayed by the brief government shutdown will be released next week, the Bureau of Labor Statistics said Wednesday.

items.title: Private payrolls rose by just 22,000 in January, far short of expectations, ADP says
items.description: The U.S. labor market barely budged in January, with hiring below even muted expectations.

items.title: Trump refuses to be outdone by Europe, signing his own U.S.-India trade deal
items.description: The U.S. deal comes after global trading partners have been signing trade pacts, leaving America looking ostracized and more isolated.

items.title: From PopMart to JD.com: Britain and China rush to forge business deals as diplomatic thaw takes hold
items.description: Chinese firms moved to pledge hundreds of millions of investment in the U.K. as Starmer's visit to China spurred a flurry of business deals and money ...

items.title: Friday's jobs report will be delayed because of the partial government shutdown
items.description: Following last year's record shutdown, the BLS also was forced to delay a number of its releases.
